  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a sysadmin/dev, I want to reduce the amount of logging on full/fast sync (at default logging level) so that I don't exceed my company's logging limits. \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\nAt default logging level (INFO):\r\n* fast sync < 5,000 messages per hour \r\n* full sync < 5,000 messages per hour\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\nstart a new full sync or fast sync node\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\n<5,000 messages per hour\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\r\n>11,000 log messages per hour\r\n\r\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?]\r\n100%\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: [`besu --version`]\r\n22.1.0\r\n* Java version: [`java -version`]\r\n* openjdk version \"11.0.11\" 2021-04-20 LTS\r\n* OS Name & Version: [`cat /etc/*release`]\r\n* NAME=\"Amazon Linux\"\r\nVERSION=\"2\"\r\nID=\"amzn\"\r\nID_LIKE=\"centos rhel fedora\"\r\nVERSION_ID=\"2\"\r\nPRETTY_NAME=\"Amazon Linux 2\"\r\nANSI_COLOR=\"0;33\"\r\nCPE_NAME=\"cpe:2.3:o:amazon:amazon_linux:2\"\r\nHOME_URL=\"https://amazonlinux.com/\"\r\nAmazon Linux release 2 (Karoo)\r\n* Kernel Version: [`uname -a`]\r\namzn2.x86_64 #1 SMP Wed Apr 1 18:06:08 UTC 2020 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n* Cloud VM, type, size: [Amazon Web Services I3-large]\r\nmakes no difference\r\n",
